verbose_text: While some plants did not produce detectable levels of E-2-HAL in our assays, damage induced production in other plants ranged from 149 +/- 38 ng/g FW (Monstera sp.) up to 78,485 +/- 24,399 ng/g FW in Vigna radiata leaves, and it appears as if E-2-HAL is the major compound in the highly emitting plants.
